Conjectured by Erdos and Faudree, who showed that $2^{n/2}<f(n) \leq 2^{n-2}$. The first problem was solved by Verstra"{e}te \cite{Ve04}, who proved $ f(n)\ll 2^{n-n^{1/10}}. $ This was improved by Nenadov \cite{Ne25} to $ f(n) \ll 2^{n-n^{1/2-o(1)}}. $ One can also ask about the existence and value of $\lim f(n)^{1/n}$.
